==English==
===Pronunciation===
<!--Note that the syllables are "in" and "cline", so the sound in the first syllable is "n", not "ng"-->
*(''verb''): ĭnklīn', /ɪnˈklaɪn/, /<tt>In"klaIn</tt>/
*(''noun''): ĭn'klīn, /ˈɪnklaɪn/, /<tt>"InklaIn</tt>/
[[Category:English heteronyms]]

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|incline|inclines|inclined|inclining}}

# To [[bend]] or move (something) out of a given plane or direction, often the [[horizontal]] or [[vertical]].
#:''He had to incline his body against the gusts to avoid being blown down in the storm.''
#:''The people following the coffin inclined their heads in grief.''

