===Intransitive verb===
{{en-verb|incline|inclines|inclined|inclining}}[[Category:English verbs]]

#To [[slope]].
#:''Over the centuries the wind made the walls of the farmhouse incline.''
# To [[habitual]]ly [[tend]].
#:''He inclines to believe anything he reads in the newspapers.''
<!--same meaning as above
#To [[tend]] to do something, or move in a certain direction, away from a [[point of view]], [[attitude]], etc.-->
#:''I'm inclined to give up smoking after hearing of the risks to my health.''

====Usage notes====
#In the sense "to habitually tend", '''incline''' is usually used in the [[passive voice]].

